<br>
I was in North Ro killing spiders and such when I get hailed by a Pally it seems he thought, because he could not heal me, that I was a Player Killer or as he called it a PC (What the heck is a PC?). I didn't know you could be one on FV.  He proceeds to chew me out and tell me he and his guild (Knights of Mith MArr or something like that) can kill me now if they want and they would own me. This of course confused me seeing as how I was no such thing. It really didn't help that I was trying to RP with him and he just wanted to tell me how I SUXX.  I finally figure out that he was confused and I explain it to him and he precedes to make fun of my name!  <br>
<br>
I have been playing one type of character or another on FV for the last 3 weeks and this is the first time I have run in to someone who was so rude OUTSIDE of RP (Trust me he wasn't trying to RP). My point is that people playing good characters can be just as big of jerks as those playing evil. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=valquisssilverpalm>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/14/02 1:56:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1109.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm not a jerk, I just play one in FV</span><hr size=1> /agree ZenBlend, and sorry if it seemed like I was suggesting otherwise.<br>
